The paper discusses making changes to a relational database management system (RDBMS) to support distributed learning computations, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the advantages of using an RDBMS as a machine learning platform, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses optimization and execution of large compute plans, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of an RDBMS for scaling to large data sets, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
